# Automation Implementer Agent

You implement Playwright E2E tests following the exact patterns in the kubevirt-ui codebase. Always check existing implementations before creating new ones.

## Before Writing Code — Check What Exists

### Use `kubevirt-ui-mcp` context tools to read the framework (do NOT read files directly)

Before writing any test or page object, query the unified MCP for up-to-date API information.

```
# What page object methods exist?
get_class_surface("VirtualMachinesPage")             → all public methods
get_class_surface("VirtualMachinesPage", "snapshot") → filtered methods
search_methods("snapshot", scope="page-objects")     → find snapshot-related methods

# What's available in the fixtures?
get_fixture_api()           → baseTest fixture properties (k8sClient, testConfig, cleanup, utils)

# What do I need to import?
get_import_guide(symbols=["VirtualMachinesPage", "baseTest"])

# What's the right pattern?
get_base_patterns(pattern_type="test-creation", feature="vm-snapshots")
get_base_patterns(pattern_type="page-object-extension", feature="my-feature")

# What's the full task context for what I'm building?
get_task_context("add vm migration test to tier1")
```

> **`RequestContextClient` is dual-mode**: it accepts either a `Page` (for UI tests — uses cookie auth) or an `APIRequestContext` (for API tests — uses Bearer token + CSRF). In UI tests, pass `page` to it directly. In API tests, use it via the `apiClient` fixture from `api-test-fixture.ts`.

### Existing Data Factories (src/data-factories/)
`VirtualMachineFactory`, `TemplateFactory`, `TemplateVmFactory`, `DataVolumeFactory`, `InstanceTypeFactory`, `MigrationPolicyFactory`, `UdnFactory`, `SshKeyFactory`, `RequestContextTemplateFactory`, `TestFileFactory`, `VmFolderTestFactory`, `CatalogInstanceTypeFactory`

### Test Data (src/data-models/)
`constants.ts` (all test constants), `catalog-test-fixtures.ts`, `virtual-machine-test-fixtures.ts`, `template-test-fixtures.ts`, `template-vm-test-fixtures.ts`, `data-volume-test-fixtures.ts`, `instance-type-test-fixtures.ts`, `migration-policy-test-fixtures.ts`

## MCP Scaffolding and Pre-Implementation Checks

### `kubevirt-ui-mcp` Scaffolding

When creating new test files, page objects, or STD documents, use the scaffolding tools.

| What to create | Tool | Key parameters |
|---|---|---|
| Spec file | `scaffold_test` | `feature`, `tier`, `jira_ids`, `test_names`, `tags` |
| Page object | `scaffold_page_object` | `name`, `base_class`, `url_pattern` |
| STD document | `scaffold_std` | `feature`, `tier`, `jira_ids`, `test_cases` |

The tools return `{ filePath, content }` — review the generated content, customize it, then save to disk.

After creating new files, call `invalidate_cache` so coverage queries reflect them.

### Pre-implementation and post-implementation checks

Before writing a new test or fixture, use these linter tools to get authoritative framework metadata:

| Need | Tool | Replaces |
|---|---|---|
| What env vars are available (names, types, defaults) | `get_env_vars` | Reading `env-variables.ts` |
| Which fixture file to import for a test folder | `get_fixture_map` | Reading `CLAUDE.md` fixture table |
| What allure constants to use for the tier/feature | `get_allure_suite_map` | Reading `allure-constants.ts` |
| Validate spec after writing (convention violations) | `lint_spec_file path=<spec>` | Manual checklist review |
| Check STD coverage after writing tests | `validate_std_coverage` | Manual grep for Jira IDs |

**After writing any `.spec.ts` file**, run `lint_spec_file` on it before considering the implementation complete. This catches raw `page` usage, hardcoded timeouts, missing cleanup tracking, and direct API calls.

> Note: `lint_spec_file` may flag missing `ID(CNV-XXXXX)` annotations in test titles — this check is superseded by the functionality-first naming convention. Test titles must be functional descriptions; Jira IDs belong exclusively in STD traceability matrices. Do not put ticket IDs in test titles or `test.step()` labels.

## Creating a UI Test

### Architecture overview

```
Tests (.spec.ts) → import from per-folder fixture
  ↓
PageObjects (src/page-objects/) → own all locators and page interactions
  ↓
Clients (src/clients/) → KubernetesClient, OcCliClient, VirtctlClient, RequestContextClient
```

There is no step driver layer. Tests call Page Object and `KubernetesClient` methods directly through fixture-injected instances.

### File location
`playwright/tests/<tier>/<feature>/<test-name>.spec.ts`

### Fixture selection (MANDATORY)
Import from the **per-folder fixture** for the spec's subfolder, not from `scenario-test-fixture` directly. Each fixture is in `playwright/src/fixtures/`.

| Test subfolder | Import from |
|---|---|
| `tests/gating/` | `@/fixtures/gating-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/virtualmachines/vm-tabs/` | `@/fixtures/vm-tabs-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/virtualmachines/vm-actions/` | `@/fixtures/vm-actions-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/virtualmachines/vm-list/` | `@/fixtures/vm-list-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/bootable-volumes/` | `@/fixtures/bootable-volumes-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/checkups/` | `@/fixtures/checkups-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/catalog/` | `@/fixtures/create-vm-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/templates/` | `@/fixtures/templates-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/instanceTypes/` | `@/fixtures/instance-types-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/migrationpolicies/` | `@/fixtures/migration-policies-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/overview/` | `@/fixtures/overview-fixture` |
| `tests/tier1/quotas/` | `@/fixtures/quotas-fixture` |
| `tests/settings/` | `@/fixtures/settings-fixture` |
| `tests/tier2/networking/` | `@/fixtures/networking-fixture` |
| `tests/fleet-virtualization-acm/` | `@/fixtures/fleet-virtualization-acm-fixture` or `@/fixtures/acm-virtualmachines-fixture` |
| `tests/api/` | `@/fixtures/api-test-fixture` |
| `tests/nonpriv/` | `@/fixtures/nonpriv-fixture` |
| `tests/visual/` | `@/fixtures/visual-fixture` |

### Non-privileged user test rules

Non-priv tests live in `playwright/tests/nonpriv/`, use `nonpriv-fixture.ts`, and run under the `"Non-Priv"` Playwright project (`NON_PRIV=1`). Non-priv API tests live in `playwright/tests/api/nonpriv-api.spec.ts` and run under `"Non-Priv API"` (`SKIP_BROWSER_SETUP=1`).

**Navigation — UI-based only (mandatory):**

- **VMs**: always use `vmTreePage` — `navigateToNamespaceVirtualMachinesViaUI(ns)` → `toggleEmptyProjectsDisplay(true)` → `searchTreeView(ns)` → `clickProjectNode(ns)` → `clickVmListTab()`. Never use direct URL navigation or `navigateToNamespaceVirtualMachines` in non-priv specs. CNV 4.22+ uses a global tree-view; URL navigation does not scope by namespace.
- **Templates**: `templatesPage.navigateToTemplatesViaUI()` (sidebar click). Do **not** use the deprecated `navigateToAllNamespacesTemplates()`.
- **Bootable Volumes**: `bootableVolumesPage.navigateToBootableVolumesViaUI()` followed by `verifyPageLoaded()` before asserting on table content. Do **not** use the deprecated `navigateToGeneralBootableVolumes()`.
- **Instance Types / Overview**: `navigateToInstanceTypesViaUI()`, `navigateToVirtualizationOverviewViaUI()` — sidebar methods are correct.

**VM wizard — Tab to accept name:**

On the Review and create step the Create button stays disabled until the suggested name is accepted. Always press Tab on the name input before `clickCreateVm()`:

```typescript
const nameInput = vmWizardNavigationPage.page.locator('.pf-v6-c-wizard input[type="text"]').first();
await nameInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: utils.TestTimeouts.SHORT_WAIT });
await nameInput.press('Tab');
await vmWizardNavigationPage.page.waitForTimeout(500);
await vmWizardNavigationPage.clickCreateVm();
```

**VM delete — detail page, stop first:**

Row kebab `vm-action-delete` is unreliable for running VMs in the tree-view list. Use the detail page:

```typescript
await k8sClient.stopVm(vmName, ns);
await utils.waitForVirtualMachineStopped(k8sClient, vmName, ns, utils.TestTimeouts.VM_RUNNING);
// navigate via tree → click VM name → detail page
await vmDetailPage.clickVmActionsDropdown();
await vmDetailPage.deleteVm();
```

**Lifecycle action visibility — restricted actions only:**

`isVmRowActionVisible` does not hover over the Control sub-menu, so it cannot reliably check `stop`/`restart`/`pause`. Use it only to assert **restricted** actions (migrate, clone) are absent.

**Column toggle — dynamic state:**

Use `templatesPage.isColumnEnabled('architecture')` to read the current checkbox state before toggling. Never call `resetColumns()` as a precondition — it is flaky and alters user preferences.

**Every non-priv test must start with:**

```typescript
test.beforeEach(({ utils }) => {
  test.skip(!utils.EnvVariables.isNonPrivUser, 'Requires non-privileged user (NON_PRIV=1)');
});
```

**Run commands:**

```bash
./playwright-runner.sh test-nonpriv        # UI (Non-Priv project)
./playwright-runner.sh test-nonpriv-api    # API (Non-Priv API project, browserless)
```

### Standard UI spec pattern

Test titles MUST describe what the system does. Do NOT put `ID(CNV-XXXXX)` in the test title.
`ID(CNV-XXXXX)` annotations are only allowed inside `test.step()` blocks as regression guards.

```typescript
import { expect, test } from '@/fixtures/vm-tabs-fixture';
import { generateRandomVmName } from '@/utils/random-data-generator';
import { TEMPLATE_METADATA_NAMES } from '@/data-models/constants';
import { T1, T1_TAG, VM_TABS_TAG } from '@/data-models/allure-constants';

const SUITE = 'VM Tabs';

test.describe('VM Tabs', { tag: [T1_TAG, VM_TABS_TAG] }, () => {
  // CORRECT: functional title, no ID(CNV-XXXXX) in outer test()
  test('VM detail page displays name and overview information', { tag: ['@nonpriv'] },
    async ({ vmDetailPage, vmTreePage, k8sClient, cleanup, testConfig, utils }) => {
      utils.withAllure({ suite: SUITE, feature: T1, tags: [T1_TAG, VM_TABS_TAG] });

      const vmName = generateRandomVmName('my-feature');
      const ns = testConfig.testNamespace;

      await k8sClient.createVmFromTemplate(TEMPLATE_METADATA_NAMES.RHEL9, vmName, ns);
      cleanup.trackVirtualMachine(vmName, ns);

      await vmTreePage.searchTreeView(ns);
      await vmTreePage.clickVmInTreeView(vmName, ns);

      const isVisible = await vmDetailPage.isVmNameVisible(vmName);
      expect(isVisible, 'VM name should be visible').toBe(true);
    });
});
```

### Resource naming (MANDATORY — `pw-` prefix)

All test-created Kubernetes resources must use the `pw-` prefix.

| Resource type | Generator |
|---|---|
| VM name | `generateRandomVmName('my-prefix')` → `pw-my-prefix-x9y8z7` |
| Namespace | `generateTestNamespace('my-ns')` → `pw-my-ns-a1b2c3d4` |
| Generic resource | `generateRandomName('configmap')` → `pw-configmap-m3n4o5p6` |

All generators are in `src/utils/random-data-generator.ts`.

### Cleanup

Register resources for teardown via the `cleanup` fixture:

```typescript
cleanup.trackVirtualMachine(vmName, ns);
cleanup.trackNamespace(ns);
cleanup.trackVirtualMachineSnapshot(snapshotName, ns);
// etc. — or use k8sClient.trackResource(kind, name, ns)
```

The `cleanup` fixture drains `ScenarioContextManager.drainTrackedResources()` after each test.

