## Creating an API Test

API tests live in `playwright/tests/api/` and use a completely different fixture. They are browserless and test HTTP contracts directly against the console proxy.

### File location
`playwright/tests/api/<feature>-api.spec.ts` (read-only) or `<feature>-crud-api.spec.ts` (CRUD)

### Fixture
```typescript
import { expect, test } from '@/fixtures/api-test-fixture';
// Provides: apiClient (RequestContextClient), k8sClient (KubernetesClient), testNamespace
```

### Read-only API spec pattern
```typescript
import { expect, test } from '@/fixtures/api-test-fixture';

test.describe('Feature page — API endpoints', () => {
  test('GET list endpoint returns correct list kind', async ({ apiClient }) => {
    const body = await apiClient.getVirtualMachines();
    expect(body.kind).toBe('VirtualMachineList');
    expect(Array.isArray(body.items)).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

### CRUD API spec pattern (dual-client)
```typescript
import { load as yamlLoad } from 'js-yaml';
import { MigrationPolicyFactory } from '@/data-factories/migration-policy-factory';
import { expect, test } from '@/fixtures/api-test-fixture';
import { generateRandomString } from '@/utils/random-data-generator';

test.describe('Resource CRUD — API', () => {
  let resourceName: string;

  test.beforeAll(async ({ apiClient, k8sClient, testNamespace }) => {
    resourceName = `pw-api-test-${generateRandomString(6, 'alphanumeric').toLowerCase()}`;

    const yaml = MigrationPolicyFactory.createMinimal(resourceName);
    await apiClient.createMigrationPolicy(yamlLoad(yaml));

    const ready = await k8sClient.waitForVmExists(resourceName, testNamespace);
    expect(ready).toBe(true);
  });

  test.afterAll(async ({ apiClient }) => {
    if (resourceName) {
      await apiClient.deleteMigrationPolicy(resourceName).catch(() => undefined);
    }
  });

  test('READ: GET returns the created resource', async ({ apiClient }) => {
    const list = await apiClient.getMigrationPolicies();
    const found = list.items.find((p: any) => p.metadata.name === resourceName);
    expect(found).toBeDefined();
  });
});
```

### Dual-client strategy (MANDATORY for CRUD specs)

| Operation | Client | Why |
|---|---|---|
| CREATE, PATCH, DELETE | `apiClient` (console proxy) | Tests the exact HTTP endpoint the UI uses |
| Wait after CREATE | `k8sClient.waitForVmExists()` etc. | Reliable polling, no CSRF |
| Wait after DELETE | `k8sClient.waitForVmDeleted()` | Confirms resource gone before next assertion |
| Read assertions | `apiClient.get*()` | Validates the proxy endpoint returns correct data |

### Running API tests
```bash
SKIP_BROWSER_SETUP=1 npm run test-playwright -- --project="API Tests"
SKIP_BROWSER_SETUP=1 npm run test-playwright -- --project="API Tests" playwright/tests/api/vm-crud-api.spec.ts
```

### Bidirectionality checklist (MANDATORY)

**When adding a UI test:**
1. Identify write operations (create, patch, delete console-proxy endpoints)
2. Check `playwright/tests/api/` for a matching `*-crud-api.spec.ts`
3. If none exists → create it or file an explicit coverage gap comment

**When adding an API spec:**
1. Include a `Mirrors the UI test operations in:` header comment naming the UI spec(s)
2. Add a row to `playwright/docs/api/api-tests.md` §5

