## Creating a Per-Folder Fixture

When a new test subfolder needs its own fixture:

1. Create `playwright/src/fixtures/<folder>-fixture.ts`
2. Import `{ baseTest }` from `@/fixtures/scenario-test-fixture`
3. Define a TypeScript interface for the new fixture properties
4. Call `baseTest.extend<{...}>({ ... })` to add POs and clients
5. Export `test` and re-export `expect` from the base fixture

```typescript
import { baseTest } from '@/fixtures/scenario-test-fixture';
import MyPage from '@/page-objects/my-page';
import OtherPage from '@/page-objects/other-page';

interface MyFixtures {
  myPage: MyPage;
  otherPage: OtherPage;
}

const test = baseTest.extend<MyFixtures>({
  myPage: async ({ page }, use) => {
    await use(new MyPage(page));
  },
  otherPage: async ({ page }, use) => {
    await use(new OtherPage(page));
  },
});

export { test };
export { expect } from '@/fixtures/scenario-test-fixture';
```

The base `baseTest` already provides `k8sClient`, `testConfig`, `cleanup`, `utils`, and `page`.

