## KubernetesClient (MANDATORY)

All Kubernetes cluster communication goes through `KubernetesClient`. Each worker gets a single instance via the `k8sClient` fixture.

### Handler Architecture

| Handler | Property | Domain |
|---------|----------|--------|
| `VirtualMachineHandler` | `client.vm` | VM/VMI lifecycle, patches, disks, features |
| `NamespaceHandler` | `client.namespace` | Namespace CRUD, RBAC grants |
| `TemplateHandler` | `client.template` | OpenShift template operations |
| `DataVolumeHandler` | `client.dataVolume` | DataVolume, DataSource |
| `SecretConfigMapHandler` | `client.secret` | Secrets, ConfigMaps, PVCs |
| `NodeHandler` | `client.node` | Node queries, cordon/uncordon |
| `HyperConvergedHandler` | `client.hco` | HCO settings, migration limits |
| `SnapshotHandler` | `client.snapshot` | VM snapshots, volume snapshots |

When adding new K8s methods, add them to the appropriate handler, not to `KubernetesClient` directly.

