## Functionality-First Test Naming (MANDATORY)

### Rule

Test titles describe **what the system does**, not which Jira ticket introduced the feature:

```typescript
// CORRECT — functional description
test('Migration and descheduler widgets are visible on cluster overview', ...)
test('VM detail tabs render expected content for a running VM', ...)
test('Bootable volumes name filter narrows results and clears correctly', ...)

// WRONG — ticket-first (do not use)
test('ID(CNV-81764) Migration and descheduler widgets', ...)
test('ID(CNV-87321) Bootable volumes name filter clears correctly', ...)
```

Ticket IDs belong **exclusively in STD documents** (Requirements Traceability Matrix). They must not appear in test titles, step labels, or test body code.

### When to use `test.step()`

Use `test.step()` to group assertions that verify a distinct logical aspect of a feature. Step labels describe **what is being verified**, not which ticket introduced it:

```typescript
// CORRECT: functional outer test title; functional step labels inside
test('Migration and descheduler widgets are visible on cluster overview', async ({ virtualMachinesPage, utils }) => {
  utils.withAllure({ suite: SUITE, feature: GATING, tags: [GATING_TAG] });

  await virtualMachinesPage.navigateToVirtualizationOverviewViaUI();

  await test.step('Migration section heading reads "Migration statuses"', async () => {
    const title = await virtualMachinesPage.getMigrationStatusSectionTitle();
    expect(title).toBe('Migration statuses');
  });

  await test.step('Guest agent widget title reads "Guest agent status"', async () => {
    const title = await virtualMachinesPage.getGuestAgentWidgetTitle();
    expect(title).toBe('Guest agent status');
  });
});
```

### When NOT to use `test.step()`

Do NOT wrap procedural steps, navigation, setup, or sequential actions in `test.step()`. Write the implementation inline.

```typescript
// WRONG: test.step() as a comment substitute / sequential narrative
await test.step('Navigate to VM list and open wizard', async () => {
  await virtualMachinesPage.navigateToVirtualMachinesViaUI();
  await createVmPage.openCreateVmWizard();
});

// CORRECT: implementation inline, no wrappers
await virtualMachinesPage.navigateToVirtualMachinesViaUI();
await createVmPage.openCreateVmWizard();

// WRONG: test.step() for resource setup
await test.step('Create namespace and VM', async () => {
  namespace = generateTestNamespace('storage');
  vmName = generateRandomVmName('storage');
  await k8sClient.createNamespace(namespace);
});

// CORRECT: setup inline
const namespace = generateTestNamespace('storage');
const vmName = generateRandomVmName('storage');
await k8sClient.createNamespace(namespace);
```

### Summary rule

| Step type | Use `test.step()`? |
|---|---|
| Bugfix regression assertion: `ID(CNV-XXXXX) ...` | **Yes** — with ticket ID in step title |
| Navigation, setup, resource creation | **No** — inline |
| Sequential flow description | **No** — inline |
| General assertions (not tied to a specific ticket) | **No** — inline |

Do NOT write separate `test()` blocks for different aspects of the same functional scenario. Consolidate into one `test()` with inline assertions or targeted `test.step()` regression guards.

