## GTS Compliance (TypeScript Style)

- **`noImplicitOverride`** — use `override` modifier on every method/property that overrides a base class member.
- **`useUnknownInCatchVariables`** — `catch (error)` is `unknown`. Use `error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error)`.
- **`prefer-const`** — `const` by default; `let` only when reassigned.
- **`@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`** — avoid `any`; use `unknown` + type guards.
- **`consistent-type-imports`** — use `import type` for type-only symbols.
- **`consistent-type-definitions`** — prefer `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions/intersections.
- **`readonly`** — mark all class fields never reassigned after construction.
- **Default exports** — page objects use `export default class`. Everything else uses named exports.

---

## Page Encapsulation Policy (MANDATORY)

**`page` must NEVER be used directly in test files.** All Playwright `page` interactions must be encapsulated inside page objects.

```typescript
// WRONG: destructuring page in test
test('example', async ({ page, virtualMachinesPage }) => {
  await page.locator('[data-test="vm-list"]').click();
  expect(page.url()).toContain('tab=vms');
});

// CORRECT: everything through page objects
test('example', async ({ virtualMachinesPage }) => {
  await virtualMachinesPage.clickVmList();
  const url = await virtualMachinesPage.getCurrentUrl();
  expect(url).toContain('tab=vms');
});
```

Exception: `page.goto()` is acceptable in tests for deep-link navigation when no UI path exists, but always prefer page object `navigate*` methods.

---

## Navigation Policy (MANDATORY — UI-first)

Navigation MUST use UI interactions (sidebar clicks, tree view, tab switches) as the primary path.

- **Test files**: Use PO navigation methods like `navigateToVirtualMachinesViaUI()`, never raw `page.goto()`
- **Page objects**: `*ViaUI` methods preferred; `goTo()` in `catch` blocks as fallback only

---

## Serial Mode Policy

**Default: parallel.** Do NOT add `test.describe.configure({ mode: 'serial' })` unless a concrete reason exists (shared cluster-level singleton mutation).

---

## Selectors

- Prefer `[data-test="..."]` or `[data-test-id="..."]`
- Use semantic ARIA (`role`, `getByRole`) when no data attribute exists
- Never use CSS class selectors (`.pf-*`)

