## Visual Regression Tests (`playwright/tests/visual/`)

Visual tests are a distinct test type — different fixture, different assertion style, different constraints. When working on `playwright/tests/visual/` or related infrastructure, apply these rules in addition to the general patterns above.

### Key differences from functional UI tests

| Aspect | Functional UI test | Visual regression test |
|---|---|---|
| Fixture | Per-folder fixture (e.g. `vm-tabs-fixture`) | `@/fixtures/visual-fixture` |
| Assertion | `expect(x).toBe(true)` | `toHaveScreenshot('name.png', ...)` |
| Mock strategy | Optional (uses live cluster data) | Mandatory — all data intercepted via `VisualMockPage` |
| Resource creation | Allowed (via `cleanup.track*`) | Forbidden — no cluster writes |
| Allure tags | `T1_TAG`, `GATING_TAG`, etc. | `VISUAL_TAG` only |
| Project | Gating / Tier 1 / etc. | `Visual` |

### Mandatory rules for visual specs

1. **Import from `@/fixtures/visual-fixture`** — never from `scenario-test-fixture` or `gating-fixture`
2. **`page.route()` only through `VisualMockPage`** — call `visualMockPage.mock*Api()`, never inline route in spec
3. **Intercepts before navigation** — register all mocks before `navigateTo*ViaUI()`
4. **`waitForPageSettle()` before screenshot** — always call `await visualMockPage.waitForPageSettle()` after navigation
5. **Element-level screenshots** — prefer scoped locators (`table`, `[role="tablist"]`, `[role="dialog"]`) over `page`
6. **Mask dynamic content** — always pass `mask: [page.locator('time'), ...]` for timestamps
7. **Dialogs open, never submitted** — take screenshot of open dialog, then close with Cancel/Escape
8. **`test.skip()` for absent elements** — guard optional UI features with a visibility check + `test.skip()`
9. **No `ID(CNV-XXXXX)` in test titles** — visual tests do not map to Jira tickets

### Adding a new visual mock

When a new module needs a mock not yet in `VisualMockPage`:

```typescript
// 1. Add payload to src/utils/visual-mock-data.ts
export const MOCK_QUOTAS_RESPONSE = { apiVersion: '...', kind: 'List', items: [...] };

// 2. Add method to src/page-objects/visual/visual-mock-page.ts
public async mockQuotasApi(): Promise<void> {
  const handler = (route: Route) => VisualMockPage._jsonReply(route, MOCK_QUOTAS_RESPONSE);
  await this._addRoute(/\/api\/kubernetes\/apis\/aaq\.kubevirt\.io\/v1alpha1\/applicationsresourcequotas/, handler);
}
```

